#: ../../manual/game_engine/performance.rst:4
msgid "Performance Considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/performance.rst:6
msgid ""
"When developing games, game engineers, software and hardware developers uses "
"some tools to fine tune their games to specific platforms and operating "
"systems, defining a basic usage scenario whereas the users would have the "
"best possible experience with the game."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/performance.rst:10
msgid ""
"Most of these tools, are software tools available for the specific Game "
"Engines whereas the games were being developed and will run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/performance.rst:13
msgid ""
"Blender Game Engine also comes with some visual tools to fine tune the games "
"being developed, so the game developers could test the best usage scenario "
"and minimum software and hardware requirements to run the game."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/game_engine/performance.rst:17
msgid ""
"In Blender, those tools are available at the *System* and *Display* panel of "
"*Render* tab in the *Properties editor*. There are options for specific "
"performance adjusts and measurements, ways to control the frame rate or the "
"way the contents are rendered in Blender window (game viewport) while the "
"game runs, as well as controls for maintaining geometry allocated in graphic "
"cards memory."
msgstr ""

